To calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio as of the end of the reporting period (2024-02-05), we use the formula:

\[
\text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{\text{Total Liabilities}}{\text{Total Assets}}
\]

From the balance sheet:

- Total Current Liabilities = 499,821.72
- There is no explicit mention of long-term liabilities, so we assume total liabilities = total current liabilities = 499,821.72
- Total Assets = 14,890,758.71

Calculate:

\[
\frac{499,821.72}{14,890,758.71} \approx 0.03356
\]

Rounded to two decimal places: 0.03

